effective. PGE(1), PGE(2), PGF(1)(alpha), and PGF(3)(alpha) not only attenuated 
chemical-induced diabetes mellitus but also restored the antioxidant status to 
normal range in red blood cells and pancreas. These results suggest that PGE(1), 
PGE(2), PGF(1)(alpha), and PGF(3)(alpha) can abrogate chemically induced 
diabetes mellitus in experimental animals and attenuate the oxidant stress that 
occurs in diabetes mellitus.

