The significant advances achieved in the management of HIV disease, thanks to 
highly active antiretroviral therapy, are at risk of being frustrated by the 
recent changes in the cost reimbursement rules for all lipid-lowering drugs 
available in Italy. Unfortunately, the remarkably increased life expectancy 
achieved since mid-1996 by HIV-infected persons after the introduction of 
protease inhibitors and combined anti-HIV treatment, is accompanied by 
significant risks of developing diet-uncontrolled hypercholesterolemia and/or 
