When newborn infants are bound to die.

Saugstad OD(1).

Author information:
(1)Department of Pediatric Research, University of Oslo, Oslo, Norway. 
o.d.saugstad@medisin.uio.no

Comment on
    Acta Paediatr. 2005 Nov;94(11):1626-31.

Withholding and withdrawing of intensive care of severely ill newborns may 
occasionally be needed when there is severe injury and extremely poor prognosis. 
In such cases, strict guidelines and procedures should be followed. In this 
issue of Acta Paediatrica, Arlettaz et al. describe such guidelines and report 
